183
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,750
You’re paranoid.

184
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:48,070
Everything is fine, isn’t it?

185
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,070
What do you know?

186
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,040
Without Count Cheng’an,

187
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,470
we’d be in grave danger.

188
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:54,110
You’d better

189
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,750
prepare gifts

190
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:56,800
to thank him.

191
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,040
Heng is right.

192
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,590
That’s our top priority.

193
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,040
Bad news, Young Master!

194
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:09,110
How many times

195
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:11,070
have I told you

196
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:12,160
to stay calm at all...

197
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:13,440
times?

198
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,470
May I ask...

199
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,800
I’m here to see Huahua.

200
00:11:30,470 --> 00:11:31,470
That’s too kind of you

201
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,750
to come with so many gifts.

202
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:34,560
I like the cat.

203
00:11:34,950 --> 00:11:36,230
They’re all for Huahua.

204
00:11:37,350 --> 00:11:38,070
Ban Heng.

205
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:38,710
Coming.

206
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:41,350
Let’s go. Come.

207
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:48,470
Hurry!

208
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:54,470
Huahua,

209
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,350
it must be tough

210
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:57,870
living with

211
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,520
such a quiet handler.

212
00:12:02,070 --> 00:12:03,070
You think so, too?

213
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,590
She’s even making a move on a cat.

214
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,920
My sister came for you.

215
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:11,920
Stop pretending.

216
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:20,800
My cat seems to like you.

217
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,070
Generally speaking,

218
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:25,400
both humans and cats

219
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:26,680
find me likable.

220
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:28,200
Those

221
00:12:28,470 --> 00:12:29,400
who’re dull,

222
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:31,640
seemingly aloof

223
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:33,560
and scheming

224
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:34,470
are the only exceptions.

225
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:35,750
Count Cheng’an,

226
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:37,520
which category are you in?

227
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,830
I always appreciate

228
00:12:44,990 --> 00:12:46,470
an honest free spirit like you.

229
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:48,470
So do you like me or not?

230
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:49,710
You’re making me confused.

231
00:12:50,110 --> 00:12:51,640
You’re such a straight shooter.

232
00:12:53,590 --> 00:12:54,400
Let’s go.

233
00:12:58,470 --> 00:12:59,750
For good judges of character,

234
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:01,520
it’s impossible to not like you.

235
00:13:02,070 --> 00:13:03,680
Don’t sweet-talk me.

236
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:05,750
Someday, I’ll crack you.

237
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,280
Eat up.

238
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:10,230
Don’t be

239
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:11,830
like those bony nerds.

240
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:13,350
What’s wrong with them?

241
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:14,750
They’re quiet and considerate

242
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,040
without showing others their claws.

243
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,160
So much better

244
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,520
than a violent-tempered

245
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:19,320
and untamed kitty, isn’t it?

246
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:21,830
So what if it’s loud

247
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:23,040
and has a temper?

248
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:25,710
Must everyone

249
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:27,400
be a mute fox?

250
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:28,950
A nerd

251
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,200
or a mute fox,

252
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:32,560
you should know what Huahua thinks

253
00:13:32,830 --> 00:13:34,870
even if he doesn’t tell you, right?

254
00:13:35,830 --> 00:13:37,280
How could I? I’m not a mind-reader!

255
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:43,920
I’m not a cat.

256
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,350
It can’t be me, either.

257
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,160
Ban Heng! Ban Heng!

258
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:51,070
Ban Heng! Ban...

259
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:52,750
Here.

260
00:13:52,870 --> 00:13:54,160
There’s a crowd outside your mansion.

261
00:13:54,590 --> 00:13:55,640
What are they doing there?

262
00:13:55,990 --> 00:13:57,350
To propose marriage to your sister.

263
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,040
This is

264
00:14:07,070 --> 00:14:10,800
the Yans’ family heirloom for 100 years.

265
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:13,440
It’s too generous of them

266
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:15,680
to offer this simply for proposal.

267
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:20,870
Mrs. Yan loves his son dearly.

268
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:23,160
I’ve long heard

269
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:25,070
about that.

270
00:14:25,470 --> 00:14:27,350
The bracelet is to welcome Princess

271
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:30,750
into Prime Minister’s family.

272
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:33,830
It’s good.

273
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:35,950
Their son isn’t too bad.

274
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,320
But his mother is a problem.

275
00:14:37,590 --> 00:14:39,470
Rocky, give it back.

276
00:14:39,710 --> 00:14:40,470
Show her out.

277
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:41,470
Please.

278
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:45,800
Count, why are you out with me?

279
00:14:48,110 --> 00:14:48,920
I don’t

280
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:50,750
want you to feel bored.

281
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:53,640
Would you like to hear a story?

282
00:14:54,590 --> 00:14:56,110
Go ahead. I’m listening.

283
00:14:57,990 --> 00:14:59,160
Once upon a time,

284
00:14:59,590 --> 00:15:00,950
a bird fairy nested in the mountain,

285
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,350
while a bird hunter

286
00:15:02,590 --> 00:15:03,750
lived at the foot.

